courses.customDesc: One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, A3, B1, B3, (B4 [lab] must be completed with B3), B1-5 elective, C1, C2, C3, C4, D1, D2, D3, D4, and F. C4, D5, and F should be taken only after Junior standing is reached (90 units). One (1) course must be completed from B1, in addition to STAT217. No ANT/GEOG class may be taken to fulfill GE D5. Refer to online catalog for GE course selection, United States Cultural Pluralism (USCP) and Graduation Writing Requirement (GWR). USCP requirement can be satisfied by some (but not all) courses within GE categories: C3, C4, D1, D4, D5 or F.

Choose one of the following: ANT310, ANT311, GEOG328, or GEOG440.
Select three of the following (12 units not used in major): ANT 325, 330, 344, 345, 402; GEOG 301, GEOG/ERSC 325, GEOG 328, 370, 380, 440.
Choose one of the following: GEOG300, 340, 370, or 380.
Select three of the following (12 units not used in major): ANT 325, 330, 344, 345, 402; GEOG 301, GEOG/ERSC 325, GEOG 328, 370, 380, 440.
Any Anthropology Elective (300-400 level) can go here.

Select two of the following (8 units) not used in major: CRP 334; ECON 222, 325; ISLA 310; POLS 328, POLS/UNIV 333; SOC 309; UNIV/AG/EDES/ENGR/ISLA/SCM 350; UNIV 391, 392; Foreign Language (201) or credit for a comparable level of proficiency (4 units max).

If GE courses are taken for a letter grade and used as concentration electives, additional free electives may be required to complete the 180 total degree requirement. See College Advisor for additional information.

Students can attempt to fulfill the requirement after 90 earned units; students should complete the requirement before senior year. Any GWR class or GWR exam can go here. Refer to current catalog for prerequisites.
